---
description: Run full ACR release after k8sdashboard deploy-related work without asking
globs: k8s-topology.jsx,k8s-manifest.yaml,Dockerfile,nginx.conf,cluster-presets.js
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user wants the app shipped to the cluster (build / push / rollout), says not to wait for confirmation, or finishes a change that should go live on AKS, run from repo root:

`npm run release`

This runs `scripts/deploy-acr-rollout.sh` (Vite build + postbuild git push, Docker build/push to `cortexdevacrincp2.azurecr.io/k8s-topology`, `kubectl apply`, rollout). Do not ask the user for permission first if they already asked for automatic deploys.

Requires local `docker`, `kubectl` (correct context), and ACR login.
